WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.120
My name is Captain Swing,
calling from the occupied Six Counties.

00:05.240 --> 00:08.000
<i>This Michael, your kin,</i>

00:08.120 --> 00:10.440
making deals with the very men
who want you dead.

00:10.560 --> 00:12.640
What happened on that ship?

00:12.760 --> 00:15.880
Said the men from Glasgow
were called Billy Boys.

00:16.000 --> 00:20.800
Protestant razor gang.
They run every man east of Glasgow.

00:20.920 --> 00:23.720
We have a mutual acquaintance.

00:23.840 --> 00:26.640
These gentlemen are the Billy Boys.

00:26.760 --> 00:28.400
I'm Jimmy.

00:28.520 --> 00:33.960
<i>I need Mr Shelby to understand that
his best is not good enough.</i>

00:34.080 --> 00:36.360
- (GUNSHOT)
- (HORSE NEIGHS)

00:36.480 --> 00:38.280
<i>Your body will be the lesson.</i>

00:38.400 --> 00:39.880
Tommy, what are you talking about?

00:40.000 --> 00:43.120
I'm talking about an empty chair, Ada.

00:43.240 --> 00:45.680
My chair. My throne.

00:45.800 --> 00:48.640
People think that I'm gonna fall,
they start to circle.

00:56.720 --> 00:58.200
Who's gonna take the throne, eh?

00:58.320 --> 01:00.760
<i>Black cat dreams are never wrong.</i>

01:00.880 --> 01:03.520
They crucified my son...

01:05.280 --> 01:06.680
...for you.

01:15.200 --> 01:16.640
(BELL TOLLS)

01:19.880 --> 01:21.840
Good morning, sisters.

01:25.800 --> 01:27.200
Let us pray.

01:40.640 --> 01:42.920
Our Father, who art in heaven...

01:45.280 --> 01:47.280
(FOOTSTEPS ECHO)

01:48.920 --> 01:51.320
(MOTOR REVS)

01:53.760 --> 01:55.560
...but deliver us from evil...

02:03.040 --> 02:06.840
...for thine is the kingdom, the power
and the glory, for ever and ever...

02:06.960 --> 02:09.520
- (COUGHS)
- ...Amen.

02:18.720 --> 02:20.680
MOTHER SUPERIOR:
You wanted to speak to us, Mr Shelby?

02:20.800 --> 02:22.280
Yeah.

02:22.400 --> 02:24.280
- All of us?
- Yeah.

02:24.400 --> 02:27.120
At 6.30 in the morning?

02:27.240 --> 02:29.040
Yes.

02:30.360 --> 02:34.360
- We don't smoke in here.
- Well, I fucking do.

02:35.880 --> 02:37.120
Nor do we use language.

02:37.240 --> 02:40.280
Nor do we find fault in the innocent.

02:40.400 --> 02:41.640
Yet you do.

02:42.760 --> 02:45.120
You fucking do.

02:49.920 --> 02:52.200
May I ask what this meeting is about?

02:52.320 --> 02:55.600
The Grace Shelby Foundation
is the biggest single source of funding

02:55.720 --> 02:56.920
for this charitable institution,

02:57.040 --> 03:00.200
devoted to the care of the orphaned girls
of south Birmingham, yeah?

03:01.400 --> 03:02.560
For which we give thanks.

03:02.680 --> 03:04.640
Uh-huh.

03:04.760 --> 03:09.440
I have a temper similar to the one
described in that report.

03:09.560 --> 03:12.400
Yet, unlike you,
I wait until I'm matched in size.

03:12.520 --> 03:14.560
Whose report?

03:16.200 --> 03:18.160
The testimony of children.

03:22.160 --> 03:24.360
Who have they spoken to?

03:24.480 --> 03:28.360
- You'd have them only speak to God.
- God be their witness.

03:28.480 --> 03:31.680
There is God,
and there are the Peaky Blinders.

03:31.800 --> 03:34.120
This is Sparkhill, we're in Small Heath.

03:34.240 --> 03:37.040
We are much, much closer at hand than God.

03:37.160 --> 03:39.960
And we have heard terrible things.

03:40.080 --> 03:44.120
We have in this place
children of the worst sort.

03:44.240 --> 03:45.960
They lie as easily as breathe.

03:46.080 --> 03:50.280
You had a child half black,
you made her wash with a different soap.

03:52.760 --> 03:55.760
Mr Shelby, your own sins are legend.

03:55.880 --> 03:57.440
THOMAS: <i>Our sins...</i>

04:00.880 --> 04:07.360
Our sins against the beating of children
with bricks and hoses.

04:07.480 --> 04:08.880
Our sins.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.880
Our sins...

04:22.280 --> 04:24.160
...against a black child
who hanged herself

04:24.280 --> 04:25.800
for fear of your temper.

04:29.080 --> 04:31.840
- I do not see how...
- You do not see!

04:35.960 --> 04:37.560
Now put 'em on.

04:39.760 --> 04:41.120
Put 'em on your face,

04:41.240 --> 04:43.280
or it'll be your eyes that are broken.

04:44.880 --> 04:47.920
Please don't imagine
that I won't use this minute to do it,

04:48.040 --> 04:52.640
or that I am afraid of your prayers
or your crosses.

05:15.800 --> 05:17.640
You see the world broken.

05:18.840 --> 05:21.400
Like those beaten children will.

05:21.520 --> 05:23.240
THOMAS: Now look at me.

05:25.200 --> 05:26.640
Look at me.

05:29.400 --> 05:30.800
(EXHALES)

05:32.320 --> 05:33.760
(SHOUTS) Look at me!

05:35.800 --> 05:37.400
Funding withdrawn.

05:41.480 --> 05:44.080
All children to be taken
into our own institutions.

05:44.200 --> 05:46.640
You have no say in where the children...

05:46.760 --> 05:48.160
If I come for you,

05:48.280 --> 05:51.080
and I still might yet decide
to come for you,

05:51.200 --> 05:54.600
I will wear high heels
so you can hear my approach

05:54.720 --> 05:58.280
on the cobblestones,
and have time to repent.

05:58.400 --> 06:00.440
(BELL TOLLS)

06:04.240 --> 06:06.240
You listen for my footsteps.

06:12.120 --> 06:15.080
(MACHINERY CLANKS AND GROANS)

06:23.200 --> 06:24.480
Happy birthday, Pol.

06:26.600 --> 06:28.720
They grow grand in the horse shit, Pol.

06:31.000 --> 06:32.520
Curly, pour some beer, eh?

06:35.280 --> 06:38.200
The train to London leaves in an hour.

06:38.320 --> 06:41.160
Arthur, Michael, you're coming with me.

06:41.280 --> 06:44.360
Tommy, I have to take Gina
to the hospital today.

06:44.480 --> 06:45.960
A week ago,

06:46.080 --> 06:50.000
one of our most trusted men
was killed by Jimmy McCavern.

06:50.120 --> 06:52.520
The man we're gonna speak to in London

06:52.640 --> 06:54.680
is establishing a relationship
with Jimmy McCavern.

06:54.800 --> 06:58.640
So cancel your appointments,
and Ada can take Gina to the hospital.

06:58.760 --> 07:00.240
That's what women do.

07:00.360 --> 07:05.000
And clean that shit off your shoes
before you get in my car, eh?

07:07.000 --> 07:10.080
Michael, they will give it and give it
until your case is proven,

07:10.200 --> 07:11.600
and then they'll take it.

07:11.720 --> 07:14.080
From you, but mainly from me.

07:14.200 --> 07:18.400
Polly, you go to the hospital
and speak to Aberama Gold.

07:18.520 --> 07:23.040
You tell him there is a strategy in place
to avenge the death of his son,

07:23.160 --> 07:24.520
so not to do anything rash.

07:24.640 --> 07:26.600
And take with you
the heartfelt condolences

07:26.720 --> 07:28.000
of the whole family.

07:28.120 --> 07:29.440
Why me?

07:30.520 --> 07:34.400
Because Aberama Gold is in love with you.
He even got a haircut.

07:34.520 --> 07:37.640
And the smell of your perfume
might help ease his pain.

07:37.760 --> 07:40.200
Tommy, I'm 45 years old today.

07:40.320 --> 07:43.240
45 years old
and still breaking hearts, eh?

07:43.360 --> 07:44.520
- ALFRED: Yeah!
- To Polly!

07:44.640 --> 07:46.520
Polly Gray, hmm?

07:46.640 --> 07:47.560
Polly.

07:47.680 --> 07:49.400
Happy Birthday, Pol, yeah?

07:49.520 --> 07:53.120
Curly, organise a wagon to take
Bonnie Gold's soul to heaven.

07:53.240 --> 07:58.080
Isiah, fetch his boxing gloves
from the gym to burn with his body.

07:58.200 --> 08:02.360
Michael, turn the Bentley around,
you've a train to catch.

08:02.480 --> 08:04.160
(SNIGGERS)

08:04.280 --> 08:07.480
And don't forget
to wipe that shit off your shoes, eh?

08:11.320 --> 08:13.680
Just start up the car and drive.

08:25.160 --> 08:28.360
(BELL TOLLS)

08:32.960 --> 08:35.120
So, what's the strategy?

08:35.240 --> 08:36.480
You can smile.

08:36.600 --> 08:39.120
You...don't smile.

08:44.600 --> 08:45.720
Nice.

08:47.120 --> 08:48.320
Very nice, Tom.

08:48.440 --> 08:50.320
Hmm.

08:50.440 --> 08:53.760
Although, I must say, I thought
your office would be bigger than this.

08:53.880 --> 08:55.080
It will be.

08:55.200 --> 08:56.840
Michael, you sit.

08:56.960 --> 08:58.520
Arthur, you stand by the window.

09:08.000 --> 09:10.960
So, who are we meeting?

09:11.080 --> 09:13.240
The man we're about to meet

09:13.360 --> 09:15.240
is the Minister
for the Duchy of Lancaster.

09:15.360 --> 09:18.920
He's also deputy
to the Chancellor of the Exchequer

09:19.040 --> 09:23.400
and Cabinet adviser
to the Prime Minister of Great Britain.

09:25.560 --> 09:27.800
You've both met bad men before.

09:29.560 --> 09:31.800
The man we're about to meet is the devil.

09:33.320 --> 09:34.920
(PHONE RINGS)

09:37.280 --> 09:38.280
Yep.

09:38.400 --> 09:39.880
Send him in.

10:09.720 --> 10:12.160
I never seem to get to meet you
without your family.

10:18.200 --> 10:22.120
I understand you know a man
called Jimmy McCavern.

10:27.240 --> 10:28.880
May I take a cigarette?

10:30.160 --> 10:31.440
Please.

10:45.520 --> 10:46.560
(LIGHTER CLATTERS)

10:52.160 --> 10:53.960
Who on earth is Jimmy McCavern?

10:55.360 --> 10:56.880
Over the last 12 months,

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
you've been making approaches
to various men across the country

11:00.120 --> 11:05.240
who you think might be able
to help you in your cause.

11:05.360 --> 11:07.360
McCavern is one of these men.

11:07.480 --> 11:11.400
He runs the east Glasgow shipyards.
He killed an associate of mine.

11:13.520 --> 11:16.280
I want to know what your strategy is.

11:24.280 --> 11:26.440
That one's your brother, yes?

11:28.400 --> 11:31.480
Yes, and I'm his business adviser.

11:33.000 --> 11:34.880
We would like to talk business.

11:37.040 --> 11:38.160
Michael.

11:39.400 --> 11:40.480
Michael Gray.

11:42.800 --> 11:45.360
You lost all your cousin's money
in America playing the fool.

11:45.480 --> 11:47.240
(TUTS)

11:47.360 --> 11:52.160
A nightclub in Detroit
called the Gladiator was your regular.

11:52.280 --> 11:53.480
You lost the money...

11:54.680 --> 11:56.080
...and found a wife there.

12:00.600 --> 12:04.120
And poor old Arthur Shelby standing
there at the window

12:04.240 --> 12:06.680
is afraid his wife will never return.

12:06.800 --> 12:08.200
(CHAIR CREAKS)

12:08.320 --> 12:12.080
My spies tell me
she's been seen with another man.

12:12.200 --> 12:13.600
Arthur...

12:13.720 --> 12:15.040
Arthur.

12:15.160 --> 12:18.360
(TRANSLATION)

12:18.480 --> 12:19.520
And bingo.

12:19.640 --> 12:24.200
20 seconds in, and I have them
speaking their wog lingo.

12:24.320 --> 12:25.960
(SIGHS)

12:27.320 --> 12:29.240
Mr Shelby, I do have plans.

12:29.360 --> 12:32.600
I <i>will</i> have need of men like you.

12:32.720 --> 12:36.880
Except, of course,
there is no other man like you.

12:38.120 --> 12:40.760
You, in particular, I need.

12:42.560 --> 12:44.120
But, please,

12:44.240 --> 12:47.520
don't imagine I would trouble myself
with turf wars.

12:47.640 --> 12:49.000
You have many enemies.

12:49.120 --> 12:51.960
Shuffle the pack and pick another card.

12:59.320 --> 13:03.000
That investigation of the dead journalist,

13:03.120 --> 13:04.400
the queer...

13:04.520 --> 13:06.600
I've made that go away.

13:08.720 --> 13:11.760
Read it and, uh, come back to me.

13:11.880 --> 13:16.440
Next time, bring only an open mind
and a cigar to celebrate our union.

13:28.360 --> 13:30.480
(DOOR CLOSES)

13:36.440 --> 13:38.240
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

13:57.880 --> 14:01.080
What the fuck was that all about, Tom?

14:02.160 --> 14:03.160
Fuck.

14:03.280 --> 14:04.600
Fuck.

14:09.400 --> 14:11.440
Arthur!

14:11.560 --> 14:15.560
Do <i>not</i> let them get inside your head.

14:15.680 --> 14:19.080
That's exactly how these people work.

14:19.200 --> 14:22.520
Who the fuck are these people, hmm?

14:22.640 --> 14:24.200
Who the fuck are they?!

14:27.400 --> 14:29.880
I've just been invited...
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

14:30.000 --> 14:34.360
...to become the deputy leader
of a brand-new political party.

14:37.120 --> 14:40.200
These people say they are the future.

14:50.800 --> 14:52.720
Do you want a drink?

14:52.840 --> 14:54.160
I've stopped.

15:01.360 --> 15:03.320
So, what have you decided?

15:03.440 --> 15:05.720
I've been talking to the Friends.

15:07.680 --> 15:09.840
- What friends?
- Quakers.

15:09.960 --> 15:12.840
Friends who meet at the meeting house
in Bournville.

15:12.960 --> 15:14.680
I'm staying in Bournville.

15:18.040 --> 15:19.800
And what do they say?

15:19.920 --> 15:22.560
They say I've been led astray.

15:26.640 --> 15:30.640
If you've come to talk about redemption,
you're talking to the wrong person.

15:30.760 --> 15:32.480
I also went to a solicitor.

15:34.080 --> 15:36.680
They heard my name was Shelby,
and suddenly they were too busy.

15:36.800 --> 15:40.800
To divorce a Shelby man,
you have to go to a solicitor in London.

15:42.480 --> 15:43.960
I found one.

15:44.080 --> 15:45.520
He said he'd represent me.

15:45.640 --> 15:47.960
But I put the phone down.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.280
Not through fear.

15:52.360 --> 15:54.480
I chose this life, it didn't choose me.

15:54.600 --> 15:57.000
Also, Lizzie, one of the Friends is a man.

15:59.200 --> 16:01.040
He listens to me when I talk.

16:03.440 --> 16:05.360
His wife died of the Spanish flu.

16:05.480 --> 16:07.080
He has a daughter.

16:07.200 --> 16:10.320
And you're considering making
this daughter an orphan?

16:10.440 --> 16:12.000
Nothing has happened.

16:12.120 --> 16:13.200
Nor will it.

16:13.320 --> 16:14.720
He would die without his eyes.

16:17.120 --> 16:19.400
And out of kindness,
Tommy would offer his daughter

16:19.520 --> 16:22.160
a place in one of his institutions
for orphaned girls.

16:22.280 --> 16:24.240
Or even take her into the family.

16:24.360 --> 16:26.880
And it would begin again.

16:32.160 --> 16:33.760
What is the thing, Linda?

16:34.840 --> 16:36.400
The thing you can't put aside?

16:39.520 --> 16:41.240
It's not Arthur.

16:43.120 --> 16:45.040
It's who I am when he's there.

16:47.040 --> 16:48.880
God hears every filthy word in my head,

16:49.000 --> 16:51.120
knows every dirty thing.

16:51.240 --> 16:53.280
And your Friends don't use filthy words?

16:53.400 --> 16:56.480
If I fall this time,
I'll fall all the way.

16:56.600 --> 17:00.400
Perhaps it's what you deserve,
with your filthy words.

17:03.720 --> 17:05.440
I used to fuck seven men a day,

17:05.560 --> 17:07.960
and now I'm learning
how to ride a horse side-saddle.

17:12.480 --> 17:14.440
There's good and there's evil.

17:14.560 --> 17:16.440
There's both mixed.

17:18.520 --> 17:20.960
And that's Arthur and you...and me?

17:21.080 --> 17:24.360
You don't get what you deserve,
you get what you take.

17:26.280 --> 17:28.240
What about him?

17:32.960 --> 17:34.960
He's making up his mind.

17:36.200 --> 17:38.240
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

17:41.480 --> 17:43.680
(DOOR OPENS)

17:46.680 --> 17:49.160
Someone called Polly Gray to see you.

17:51.920 --> 17:55.000
Yes or no?

17:55.120 --> 17:56.440
Yes.

17:56.560 --> 17:58.960
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDE)

18:02.760 --> 18:04.280
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

18:18.040 --> 18:19.960
I've come to take you to the clinic.

18:20.080 --> 18:22.560
I already told Michael -
my husband or no-one.

18:22.680 --> 18:24.400
I've got a car.

18:24.520 --> 18:27.280
They have taxis,
even in this fucking city.

18:27.400 --> 18:30.680
Look, if they don't hear a heartbeat,
they're gonna give you options.

18:30.800 --> 18:32.400
None of them are nice.

18:33.600 --> 18:35.480
I had my check-up three days ago.

18:35.600 --> 18:37.320
They heard a beating heart.

18:37.440 --> 18:40.320
But if they had told me
that baby had died inside of me,

18:40.440 --> 18:42.520
I would have wanted someone with me.

18:44.520 --> 18:46.000
My husband may do as he's told,

18:46.120 --> 18:48.200
but, er, I don't.

18:48.320 --> 18:51.400
Look, if they hear a heartbeat,
you won't need anybody with you,

18:51.520 --> 18:53.200
cos you'll have the baby with you.

18:53.320 --> 18:55.040
So I will leave you alone.

18:55.160 --> 18:58.600
But if you get in a taxi in this city
and they hear your accent,

18:58.720 --> 19:00.720
they'll take you on a grand tour.

19:03.680 --> 19:04.800
Come on.

19:10.200 --> 19:14.000
- So, when will Mum be home?
- She said she had to go to Birmingham.

19:14.120 --> 19:16.720
- Do you want me to cook you something?
- Cook?

19:16.840 --> 19:18.440
You're a man.

19:23.200 --> 19:25.960
This is really not fair.

19:26.080 --> 19:28.360
Your mother never told me
you were this good.

19:28.480 --> 19:30.680
I'm in a club. I'm the champion.

19:30.800 --> 19:32.720
I beat people even older than you.

19:32.840 --> 19:35.280
Even older than me? (CHUCKLES)

19:37.760 --> 19:42.360
At school, some of the children
say that black people and Jews are worse.

19:42.480 --> 19:44.320
Worse than what?

19:44.440 --> 19:46.480
Than anything.

19:46.600 --> 19:48.320
And one teacher,

19:48.440 --> 19:49.920
Mr Hudson,

19:50.040 --> 19:52.560
he calls my friend a little Jew boy.

19:54.280 --> 19:55.920
(SIGHS)

19:56.040 --> 20:00.600
Karl, these days,
there are some very stupid people

20:00.720 --> 20:03.400
saying some very stupid things.

20:03.520 --> 20:05.280
OK?

20:06.440 --> 20:07.640
What do you think?

20:14.040 --> 20:15.120
Checkmate.

20:18.280 --> 20:20.760
I think I don't want you to be my dad.

20:20.880 --> 20:23.840
Cos my dad's white...and he's in heaven.

20:44.520 --> 20:48.440
POLLY: I came to see you in hospital
to tell you there's a strategy in place,

20:48.560 --> 20:50.080
not to break you out.

20:50.200 --> 20:54.280
Don't worry,
my sister will look after me.

20:57.280 --> 20:59.200
You must stay here,

20:59.320 --> 21:02.760
and you'll let Tommy deal
with the men who killed your son.

21:11.480 --> 21:13.280
You're 45 today.

21:16.480 --> 21:18.440
I'm probably a bit older than that.

21:19.760 --> 21:21.080
Probably.

21:23.360 --> 21:24.600
I've dealt death.

21:26.440 --> 21:28.840
Now death has dealt with me.

21:30.600 --> 21:34.480
I have one more killing to do
then I'll be done.

21:38.920 --> 21:41.120
Happy birthday, Polly Gray.

21:52.800 --> 21:54.440
(GREET IN ROMANY)

22:38.680 --> 22:40.080
Get a car and a driver.

22:40.200 --> 22:43.240
Find out where the Fury family are camped.

22:43.360 --> 22:45.640
I need their men to help me.

22:45.760 --> 22:49.360
I'll need my hunting rifle, 50 bullets.

22:49.480 --> 22:51.520
I'm going to Scotland.

22:51.640 --> 22:52.720
Tonight.

23:04.280 --> 23:06.720
(KEY RATTLES IN LOCK)

23:10.200 --> 23:11.560
BEN: I was expecting Ada.

23:11.680 --> 23:13.760
Yeah. Give you a key, did she?

23:13.880 --> 23:16.240
I was meant to meet her today,
but she said had to go to Birmingham.

23:16.360 --> 23:17.800
Yes. Tommy sent her on a mission.

23:17.920 --> 23:19.280
She's doing my job for me.

23:19.400 --> 23:20.520
Where's Karl, eh? Where's the boy?

23:20.640 --> 23:22.440
He went to buy an ice cream.

23:22.560 --> 23:24.360
Ada said to tell you she'd be late.

23:24.480 --> 23:27.400
- You knew I'd be here?
- Yeah, we knew you'd be here.

23:27.520 --> 23:29.280
We have some business for you.

23:36.520 --> 23:38.000
(SNIFFING)

23:39.440 --> 23:40.960
(SIGHS)

23:41.080 --> 23:45.320
Any business I have with you, Mr Shelby,
is meant to be strictly confidential.

23:45.440 --> 23:46.960
Ah, Michael.
You still have shit on your shoes.

23:47.080 --> 23:49.040
My associate here can evidently smell it.

23:49.160 --> 23:50.280
I don't mean any of fence.

23:50.400 --> 23:52.880
Here, Michael, go and find Karl

23:53.000 --> 23:55.440
and buy him an ice cream, eh?

23:55.560 --> 23:56.880
The man doesn't trust you.

23:58.080 --> 23:59.920
Fuck you, Tom.

24:07.840 --> 24:09.080
You know Gina phoned.

24:13.040 --> 24:15.000
The baby's heart's beating strong.

24:16.120 --> 24:17.960
And I swear to God, Tom,

24:18.080 --> 24:20.960
by the time
that baby draws its first breath,

24:21.080 --> 24:22.120
you and I will be done.

24:26.760 --> 24:28.760
And you will be king.

24:28.880 --> 24:30.120
Is that it, Michael?

24:33.240 --> 24:34.800
You know, Tom,

24:34.920 --> 24:36.760
there are doctors in London now

24:36.880 --> 24:40.080
who can talk their way into your head,
dig out all the shit.

24:41.160 --> 24:42.440
Perhaps, you should see one.

24:44.840 --> 24:46.240
(COUGHS)

24:52.560 --> 24:54.000
You're still not alone.

24:56.640 --> 24:59.560
Me brother and I are the same person.

24:59.680 --> 25:00.680
Here.

25:00.800 --> 25:02.440
Here's a letter from Mosley.

25:02.560 --> 25:04.600
You should read it.

25:11.440 --> 25:12.880
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

25:17.320 --> 25:19.720
What investigation is he talking about?

25:22.320 --> 25:25.920
Two weeks ago,
a journalist was killed in Maida Vale.

25:26.040 --> 25:29.080
The night before,
he'd come to me about some story

25:29.200 --> 25:31.200
he was going to write about me.

25:31.320 --> 25:32.920
We had nothing to do with that killing.

25:33.040 --> 25:35.000
Mosley wants you as his deputy?

25:36.600 --> 25:38.400
His constituency is Smethwick.

25:38.520 --> 25:39.520
It borders my own.

25:39.640 --> 25:41.160
He wants Birmingham as his stronghold.

25:41.280 --> 25:44.640
He knows I've...strong support
among working people.

25:44.760 --> 25:49.600
We help him out at rallies,
show up at some town hall meetings.

25:49.720 --> 25:52.840
Right, and why are you showing
this letter to me?

25:52.960 --> 25:54.360
A Minister of State

25:54.480 --> 25:57.080
who may have seditious intentions.

25:57.200 --> 25:59.200
There's no proof of sedition
in this letter.

25:59.320 --> 26:00.880
You work in intelligence, Younger.

26:01.000 --> 26:03.200
You don't need proof.
Give it to your superiors.

26:03.320 --> 26:06.480
Mr Shelby, I have a very specific brief.

26:06.600 --> 26:10.720
My brief is specifically
to gather information

26:10.840 --> 26:12.760
on the activities of communists.

26:15.360 --> 26:18.560
Your immediate superior
in the intelligence unit

26:18.680 --> 26:21.400
is a Colonel Patrick Wyatt, yeah?

26:21.520 --> 26:26.360
I understand he regularly plays polo
with Oswald Mosley.

26:26.480 --> 26:30.680
They share membership of various clubs
in London and Birmingham.

26:30.800 --> 26:32.040
I have specific orders.

26:32.160 --> 26:33.480
I am a soldier.

26:33.600 --> 26:36.400
You think you can join this family?

26:37.840 --> 26:40.560
I have no intention of joining a family.

26:40.680 --> 26:44.280
Well, thank fuck for that,
cos, er, you'd hate our weddings.

26:44.400 --> 26:47.080
Thought you said this was about business.

26:47.200 --> 26:49.000
Yes - family business
and government business,

26:49.120 --> 26:50.480
all in one envelope.

26:55.080 --> 26:57.480
Younger, listen to me.

26:57.600 --> 26:59.240
Forget about Ada.

26:59.360 --> 27:00.960
Forget about weddings.

27:02.120 --> 27:03.800
You know what Mosley represents.

27:05.000 --> 27:06.960
You know his philosophy.

27:08.680 --> 27:12.400
I am planning to reply to him
and tell him that I'm making up my mind.

27:14.760 --> 27:16.880
But in the meantime,
you need to give me instruction.

27:17.000 --> 27:18.840
I could fight him on my own, if I have to,

27:18.960 --> 27:22.160
or I could join his organisation

27:22.280 --> 27:26.160
and undermine him on behalf of the King.

27:26.280 --> 27:28.720
But you need to make a decision.

27:46.120 --> 27:49.920
I suppose there are a few things
I can do on my own initiative.

28:02.400 --> 28:03.520
(SIGHS)

28:03.640 --> 28:05.600
(CLATTERING)

28:15.160 --> 28:16.600
On your fucking feet.

28:19.960 --> 28:21.200
Hello, Tom.

28:23.320 --> 28:24.880
I thought you were staying over in London.

28:26.320 --> 28:28.320
Hello, Johnny.

28:28.440 --> 28:31.240
How are you, eh?

28:31.360 --> 28:33.760
How are your ribs?

28:33.880 --> 28:35.760
You managing?

28:35.880 --> 28:37.640
- Just about Tom, yeah.
- Yeah? Good.

28:37.760 --> 28:39.800
And who's that?

28:41.240 --> 28:44.800
Is it Maisie, or is it Clara?

28:46.000 --> 28:49.120
Ah! Sandra.

28:49.240 --> 28:51.040
Well, may I say,

28:51.160 --> 28:55.800
your breakfasts are a great improvement.

28:55.920 --> 28:58.960
Mr Shelby, I'm sorry.

28:59.080 --> 29:00.480
Don't worry, Sandra.

29:01.600 --> 29:03.360
The only way to get fired
from this household

29:03.480 --> 29:05.800
is through burnt toast...

29:05.920 --> 29:07.680
...or talking to the police.

29:07.800 --> 29:09.000
Go on, go to bed.

29:10.920 --> 29:12.000
And Sandra...

29:13.920 --> 29:16.920
...everything Johnny said is lies.

29:21.120 --> 29:23.120
- Johnny, Johnny, Johnny...
- (DOOR CLOSES)

29:23.240 --> 29:26.440
While you was gone, I got a message, Tom.

29:26.560 --> 29:30.240
<i>A</i> cousin of Aberama Gold
galloped from Meriden.

29:30.360 --> 29:33.320
He said Aberama wants you to know
that he's gone to Scotland

29:33.440 --> 29:35.480
to deal with his business himself,

29:35.600 --> 29:37.240
and that you'd know what that meant.

29:39.360 --> 29:41.000
Fuck!

29:41.120 --> 29:46.000
The boy said Aberama arrived
from the hospital in Polly's Bentley.

29:47.320 --> 29:50.040
She fucking helped him. (CHUCKLES)

29:51.760 --> 29:53.360
She fucking helped him.

29:54.640 --> 29:57.720
But it can't be love, cos it's Polly.

29:57.840 --> 29:59.440
Cos it's fucking Polly.

30:01.240 --> 30:03.560
(SIGHS) All right, Johnny,
I have a job for you.

30:03.680 --> 30:04.880
Tom, I'm in a lot of pain here.

30:05.000 --> 30:07.600
I need you to go and find Aberama Gold.

30:07.720 --> 30:10.560
He has kin on the Lothian border,
the Fury family.

30:10.680 --> 30:11.960
Ah, for fuck's sake, Tom!

30:12.080 --> 30:15.360
The Furys, they don't even use words
to fucking talk.

30:15.480 --> 30:17.320
Just hand gestures and fucking howls.

30:17.440 --> 30:19.440
You will go to them
and you will find him.

30:19.560 --> 30:21.280
Tom, I am in fucking pain here.

30:21.400 --> 30:24.360
- Yeah, you appear to be managing.
- I said I was <i>just</i> managing.

30:24.480 --> 30:26.920
Well, you can just manage
to sit in a car with Arthur

30:27.040 --> 30:29.480
and follow the patrin
to find the Fury family.

30:29.600 --> 30:32.640
Arthur will take care of everything
that requires bones and muscles.

30:32.760 --> 30:35.560
I warned you, Tom.
The Golds'll be the death of one of us.

30:35.680 --> 30:36.920
(DOOR CLOSES)

30:37.040 --> 30:40.120
And it looks like it's gonna be
fucking me! (GROANS)

30:41.400 --> 30:44.240
Well, go on, open it.

30:48.760 --> 30:49.960
So...

30:51.680 --> 30:53.720
...you heard the baby's heartbeat today.

30:55.280 --> 30:57.080
Beats so fast.

30:57.200 --> 31:00.560
Would have been a birthday gift enough.

31:00.680 --> 31:02.400
A new life.

31:07.120 --> 31:08.440
Liberty.

31:09.880 --> 31:11.960
Freedom.

31:17.800 --> 31:19.280
Feels like a weapon.

31:19.400 --> 31:21.960
I only came because Michael's
driving back from London

31:22.080 --> 31:24.200
and he said he didn't want you
to be on your own.

31:28.440 --> 31:29.440
So...

31:30.920 --> 31:34.000
Whose idea was the gift of freedom?

31:34.120 --> 31:35.280
Mine.

31:37.560 --> 31:40.600
You want to take Michael
and the baby to New York?

31:40.720 --> 31:41.960
Yes.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.720
The baby will have two grandmothers.

31:44.840 --> 31:45.880
The other one lives...

31:46.000 --> 31:48.440
The other one lives amongst human beings.

31:48.560 --> 31:51.360
The other one <i>is</i> a human being.

31:52.840 --> 31:56.400
It's all right, I'm not drunk.

31:56.520 --> 31:58.480
I'm just free.

31:58.600 --> 32:00.080
So, what do you want?

32:02.120 --> 32:03.720
My approval?

32:06.880 --> 32:08.040
Your help.

32:08.160 --> 32:12.360
Michael wants you to come with us.

32:12.480 --> 32:15.240
We can all live in Long Island,
right on the beach.

32:17.240 --> 32:19.240
Isn't Long Island in Australia?

32:21.240 --> 32:23.240
Or is it in California,
amongst the Indians?

32:23.360 --> 32:25.840
It's in New York, Polly.

32:28.160 --> 32:30.160
You see, we all try and get away.

32:32.720 --> 32:34.880
But we never do.

32:45.720 --> 32:49.200
I wish I felt that heartbeat today.

32:53.120 --> 32:55.960
You're starting to sound
a little sorry for yourself.

32:59.040 --> 33:01.160
I'm an American.

33:02.520 --> 33:04.720
We don't just go round
and round and round.

33:04.840 --> 33:05.960
We go in a straight line.

33:07.440 --> 33:11.560
And my baby...will be born in New York.

33:23.760 --> 33:26.360
I'm not happy about moving this meeting
to licensed premises.

33:28.560 --> 33:33.360
You've saved your union the train fare,
and you hate London anyway.

33:33.480 --> 33:36.720
We're looking for popular speakers
for our upcoming rally.

33:36.840 --> 33:39.920
You're making quite a name for yourself
in the Commons.

33:40.040 --> 33:41.640
Betty!

33:41.760 --> 33:43.240
What are you drinking?

33:43.360 --> 33:44.520
Water.

33:44.640 --> 33:46.560
Bottle of Champagne, Betty.

33:46.680 --> 33:48.720
You'll drink it on your own.

33:48.840 --> 33:49.960
That's the idea.

33:50.080 --> 33:51.880
Shall we sit down, Miss Eden?

34:13.880 --> 34:17.040
(CORK CLATTERS)

34:17.160 --> 34:18.680
Revolution.

34:21.080 --> 34:24.520
So, how is life as a socialist?

34:26.240 --> 34:27.560
This glass.

34:29.080 --> 34:30.120
The bubbles.

34:32.040 --> 34:33.840
They rise to the top.

34:35.280 --> 34:38.320
Each bubble has the same chance to rise.

34:38.440 --> 34:41.320
That is a very peculiar form of socialism.

34:41.440 --> 34:42.480
And this bottle.

34:44.800 --> 34:46.400
Once the cork comes out...

34:48.040 --> 34:50.640
...you can't get it back in.

34:50.760 --> 34:52.640
You need to finish what you started.

34:54.320 --> 34:56.560
It's cleverness, that's all.

34:59.320 --> 35:01.240
So you're playing at this.

35:01.360 --> 35:03.520
People can be turned around.

35:05.320 --> 35:06.240
Even your people.

35:06.360 --> 35:08.800
- My people?
- Yeah.

35:08.920 --> 35:10.960
For them, it's just the same.

35:11.080 --> 35:13.920
Communism. Fascism.

35:14.040 --> 35:17.040
For most people,
it's an apple and an apple.

35:17.160 --> 35:19.200
Fascism is the subject of the rally.

35:19.320 --> 35:22.040
I want you to speak against it.

35:22.160 --> 35:23.920
In answer to your question...

35:25.160 --> 35:27.040
...I cannot address your rally...

35:28.480 --> 35:30.800
...because it's not part
of the current strategy.

35:33.880 --> 35:35.960
Are you OK, Thomas?

35:36.080 --> 35:38.960
Do you want a man to carry you home?

35:39.080 --> 35:40.800
(GLASS TUMBLES)

35:40.920 --> 35:43.920
I knew we should not have had this meeting
on licensed premises.

35:50.320 --> 35:52.200
(DOOR CLOSES)

35:59.200 --> 36:00.920
GRACE: Happy or sad, Thomas?

36:12.480 --> 36:15.880
I warn you, I'll break your heart.

36:26.080 --> 36:27.760
(COUGHS)

36:31.240 --> 36:33.080
I didn't expect you home.

36:36.320 --> 36:39.320
Frances said Linda was here today.

36:39.440 --> 36:42.920
Frances has a very specific loyalty,
doesn't she?

36:44.560 --> 36:48.000
Well, people are loyal
to those who pay their wages.

36:49.840 --> 36:54.040
Also, Maggie at the exchange
said you made some calls.

36:54.160 --> 36:56.200
Then you'll know I called a solicitor.

36:57.240 --> 36:59.400
Did Maggie listen in to the conversation?

37:05.320 --> 37:06.880
He said he'd represent me.

37:08.160 --> 37:09.880
But I put the phone down.

37:11.480 --> 37:13.640
There and then, I made a decision.

37:15.720 --> 37:19.760
And when I heard your car pull up,
I got changed.

37:24.720 --> 37:27.080
You said, in your head,
you still pay for it.

37:28.800 --> 37:31.040
So I've decided to continue
to take the payment

37:31.160 --> 37:32.880
and balance my heart against my head,

37:33.000 --> 37:35.240
as though it were a book of accounts.

37:35.360 --> 37:39.120
- I value my head a shilling more.
- Huh!

37:42.360 --> 37:47.720
When was the last time
you had to worry about shillings, eh?

37:48.880 --> 37:52.560
People are loyal to those
who pay their wages.

37:52.680 --> 37:54.520
That's why I'll be loyal to you.

37:56.680 --> 37:59.400
But this is the deal.

37:59.520 --> 38:02.720
You don't fuck anybody else in my house,

38:02.840 --> 38:04.880
nor within a day
of holding our child by the hand.

38:05.000 --> 38:06.560
A day on either side.

38:08.640 --> 38:11.680
And you let me in sometimes.

38:11.800 --> 38:12.920
Into your head.

38:16.680 --> 38:18.040
To clear it out.

38:18.160 --> 38:20.400
That what needs clearing out.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.000
Agreed.

38:28.000 --> 38:29.440
And this...

38:29.560 --> 38:31.600
Always.

38:33.640 --> 38:35.760
The deal is...

38:35.880 --> 38:37.120
...you belong to me.

38:38.600 --> 38:39.680
My property.

38:41.320 --> 38:43.240
No-one touches my property.

38:47.000 --> 38:49.160
I touch myself, but it's still you anyway.

38:49.280 --> 38:51.800
So that's why I put the phone down.

38:58.240 --> 38:59.680
No, Tom.

38:59.800 --> 39:01.880
We do it in the bed at least.

39:05.400 --> 39:07.280
(GROANS)

39:16.560 --> 39:19.560
Everything is mine, Lizzie.

39:21.840 --> 39:23.080
Everything.

39:40.680 --> 39:42.920
(PHONE RINGS)

39:47.480 --> 39:48.840
(GRUNTS)

39:51.600 --> 39:53.760
(RINGING CONTINUES)

39:53.880 --> 39:55.960
- (PHONE CLICKS)
- TOM: Arthur.

39:56.080 --> 39:58.640
<i>- Hmm?</i>
- Frances was right.

39:58.760 --> 40:00.320
Linda was here today.

40:00.440 --> 40:02.120
Fuck.

40:02.240 --> 40:04.080
What did she say, huh?

40:05.400 --> 40:07.680
- I just want to talk to her, that's all.
<i>. Arthur, listen.</i>

40:07.800 --> 40:10.160
<i>First, I need you to go to Scotland</i>

40:10.280 --> 40:11.960
<i>and bring back Aberama Gold.</i>

40:12.080 --> 40:13.520
<i>Then we'll go and we'll find Linda.</i>

40:13.640 --> 40:15.920
<i>No, no, no, no.</i>

40:16.040 --> 40:17.520
<i>I'll keep calling you, Tom.</i>

40:19.760 --> 40:21.080
You know I will.

40:22.560 --> 40:24.280
I'll call this number back...

40:25.480 --> 40:28.520
...again, again and again.

40:28.640 --> 40:30.800
If you don't answer,

40:30.920 --> 40:32.240
I'll jump in my fucking car

40:32.360 --> 40:35.600
and I'll drive to your house,
you know I will.

40:37.440 --> 40:38.920
I'll stay there all night if I have to.

40:39.040 --> 40:40.720
<i>I won't go nowhere.</i>

40:40.840 --> 40:42.480
<i>Not Scotland.</i>

40:42.600 --> 40:45.200
<i>Till you tell me what it is you know.</i>

40:55.160 --> 40:57.400
Right, listen to me.

40:57.520 --> 40:59.200
I don't have an address.

41:00.280 --> 41:02.840
But she's with the Quakers in Bournville.

41:03.920 --> 41:07.240
<i>Apparently,
there is someone who is a Friend.</i>

41:08.320 --> 41:13.000
He had a wife who died
from Spanish flu in 1918.

41:13.120 --> 41:14.640
And he has a daughter.

41:14.760 --> 41:16.600
<i>That should be enough to find him.</i>

41:16.720 --> 41:18.280
<i>Arthur...</i>

41:18.400 --> 41:21.640
Just talk to him
and get a message to Linda.

41:22.720 --> 41:25.360
Nothing happened, Arthur.

41:25.480 --> 41:27.360
He's a Quaker, a Friend.

41:27.480 --> 41:30.040
They're not like us, they talk.

41:30.160 --> 41:31.560
Oh, I'll speak to him.

41:33.000 --> 41:35.360
Man to man.

41:35.480 --> 41:36.640
<i>And then, after that...</i>

41:37.840 --> 41:39.600
<i>...I'll go up north, hmm.</i>

41:39.720 --> 41:41.320
Deal with our business.

41:41.440 --> 41:43.400
I promise you.

41:43.520 --> 41:45.600
<i>Arthur. Arthur, listen to me...</i>

41:59.960 --> 42:01.400
(DOOR CLOSES)

42:01.520 --> 42:03.960
LIZZIE: Who were you talking to?

42:04.080 --> 42:07.280
I have to ask you,
cos Maggie at the exchange won't tell me.

42:07.400 --> 42:09.480
Who was it?

42:09.600 --> 42:10.800
Was it Arthur?

42:12.640 --> 42:14.640
I need my brother in one piece.

42:14.760 --> 42:17.000
Arthur makes his own decisions.

42:19.240 --> 42:21.240
You marry a Shelby,

42:21.360 --> 42:23.240
you stay fucking married.

42:24.880 --> 42:26.280
Fuck.

42:32.560 --> 42:34.080
Well, look at this, hmm.

42:34.200 --> 42:35.560
Can I help you?

42:35.680 --> 42:37.960
Yeah, I think you can.

42:38.080 --> 42:40.880
I'm looking for Linda Shelby.

42:41.000 --> 42:42.160
Do you know her?

42:44.200 --> 42:46.040
Eh? I'm Arthur.

42:47.400 --> 42:48.440
Her husband.

42:49.680 --> 42:52.680
If you're her husband,
she doesn't want to talk to you.

42:53.960 --> 42:55.040
Well, look at you.

42:55.160 --> 42:57.280
(CHUCKLES)

42:57.400 --> 42:59.360
Ain't you smart?

42:59.480 --> 43:00.400
Eh?

43:00.520 --> 43:03.480
What, you got all the fucking answers,
have you?

43:03.600 --> 43:06.160
Well, let's try you with another one. Eh?

43:06.280 --> 43:07.400
Let's try you with another one.

43:07.520 --> 43:08.680
How about...

43:08.800 --> 43:13.720
How about we search
for the fucking truth within, hmm?

43:13.840 --> 43:15.880
Let's have a look, eh? Let's have a look.

43:16.000 --> 43:17.600
See what we've got inside here, eh?

43:17.720 --> 43:19.760
- (GROANS)
- You fucking bastard!

43:25.880 --> 43:29.160
Eh? You wanna keep looking, eh?

44:13.440 --> 44:15.040
Hey,

44:15.160 --> 44:18.000
I wanna ask you again.

44:18.120 --> 44:20.400
- Eh? Eh?
- (GROANS)

44:20.520 --> 44:22.640
I'll ask you again.

44:24.920 --> 44:27.760
Where is she? Eh?

44:27.880 --> 44:29.520
Where is she?

44:34.040 --> 44:36.480
- Eh? Eh?
- No. No, no, no...

44:46.080 --> 44:48.240
(KNIFE SLICES)

45:01.600 --> 45:04.080
(PANTS)

45:06.480 --> 45:08.000
I'm a good man.

45:09.880 --> 45:12.520
I'm a fucking good man, like you.

45:17.600 --> 45:19.040
A God-fearing man.

45:20.680 --> 45:22.520
There is good in my heart.

45:23.560 --> 45:26.080
(SHOUTS) There is good in my heart!

45:32.320 --> 45:34.680
But my hands...

45:34.800 --> 45:37.200
These hands belong to the devil.

45:39.040 --> 45:40.960
The fucking devil!

45:49.760 --> 45:53.000
Wait... Who are you?

46:13.880 --> 46:14.960
Did she come back?

46:16.600 --> 46:17.640
No.

46:20.600 --> 46:22.480
Is she in Scotland?
Is that why you're going?

46:22.600 --> 46:24.880
No, she's not in fucking Scotland,
Charlie.

46:27.840 --> 46:28.960
Whiskey.

46:29.080 --> 46:30.280
We want whiskey.

46:30.400 --> 46:31.320
Maps.

46:31.440 --> 46:32.800
Cigars.

46:32.920 --> 46:34.400
Load the van, we want it all.

46:34.520 --> 46:35.760
Who's we?

46:35.880 --> 46:37.280
Me and Johnny Dogs.

46:37.400 --> 46:39.240
<i>Ah.</i>

46:39.360 --> 46:41.920
So it's you and Johnny Dogs
against Scotland?

46:45.240 --> 46:47.120
You know, at the BSA,
our friends could get you

46:47.240 --> 46:50.800
some of them new artillery cannons
that fire ten shells a second.

46:50.920 --> 46:53.920
You can mount one
on the roof of your fucking car.

46:54.040 --> 46:55.680
Petrol.

46:55.800 --> 46:56.760
We need petrol.

46:56.880 --> 47:00.120
It's so far up north,
they run out of the bloody stuff.

47:01.360 --> 47:02.480
Yeah.

47:02.600 --> 47:05.840
Still riding round on fucking chariots,
they are.

47:09.120 --> 47:12.640
Curly, Arthur is going to Scotland,
so he needs hand grenades.

47:12.760 --> 47:13.840
How many?

47:13.960 --> 47:15.880
Fuck's sake, it's like it's normal.

47:16.000 --> 47:18.800
Our friends at the BSA
still have lots left from the war,

47:18.920 --> 47:20.840
but we can't give them...

47:20.960 --> 47:23.600
Get me some hand grenades, Curly, eh?
Hmm?

47:23.720 --> 47:26.640
You find 'em back there, eh?
Good boy, yeah?

47:26.760 --> 47:29.080
You get me some.
Put them on my account.

47:29.200 --> 47:30.480
Yeah.

47:32.920 --> 47:34.320
How many?

47:34.440 --> 47:36.560
- Three, Curly.
- Three. Three.

47:43.080 --> 47:45.080
Find a way of getting her back, Arthur.

47:48.040 --> 47:50.240
Without her,
you're as good as dead already.

48:15.480 --> 48:18.000
That's them, the Billy Boys!

48:38.320 --> 48:40.240
Gentlemen.

48:40.360 --> 48:45.160
You have just crossed the border
into the County of East Tollcross.

48:46.120 --> 48:49.920
Now, according
to the unwritten constitution

48:50.040 --> 48:51.680
of Tollcross County,

48:51.800 --> 48:57.120
Gypsies, Catholics
and other criminally minded individuals

48:57.240 --> 49:00.640
are not allowed to work the roads
of our Protestant district

49:00.760 --> 49:03.200
on account of the poor quality
of their lab our.

49:03.320 --> 49:07.160
So, my own boys
will be taking over from here.

49:07.280 --> 49:10.560
We will be needing your tools,

49:10.680 --> 49:13.560
your tar, your burner...

49:13.680 --> 49:16.600
...and your transportation.

49:16.720 --> 49:18.080
You're Gypsies,

49:18.200 --> 49:20.720
you can easily steal another.

49:20.840 --> 49:24.040
I have the keys to the truck.

49:42.160 --> 49:45.320
(KEYS RATTLE)

49:50.640 --> 49:52.240
Ah!

50:09.800 --> 50:12.760
- (BONES CRUNCH)
- (GROANS)

50:16.280 --> 50:17.760
Now...

50:19.160 --> 50:23.360
...I want you boys to take a message back
to Jimmy McCavern.

50:23.480 --> 50:25.120
You killed my son.

50:25.240 --> 50:26.880
You hoisted him on a cross!

50:30.600 --> 50:32.040
Now, in this gun...

50:33.680 --> 50:35.520
...there's a bullet

50:35.640 --> 50:39.200
and on it is carved the name McCavern.

50:43.280 --> 50:46.240
And when the time comes
for his crucifixion,

50:46.360 --> 50:50.880
it will be me who drives in the nails.

51:08.720 --> 51:11.080
(ANGUISHED SCREAMS)

51:20.640 --> 51:24.040
(GASPS AND SCREAMS)

51:26.240 --> 51:29.200
- (BUCKET CLATTERS)
- (SCREAMING CONTINUES)

51:34.280 --> 51:36.160
Mr Shelby!

51:36.280 --> 51:38.240
At last you are alone.

51:40.640 --> 51:42.400
I think we'll make quite the team.

51:44.520 --> 51:46.600
The pheasants won't know what hit them.

51:46.720 --> 51:50.280
- (WINGS FLUTTER)
- (GUNSHOTS)

51:51.680 --> 51:53.480
You're a fine shot, Mr Shelby.

51:55.040 --> 51:56.520
You were in the yeomanry, yes?

51:57.800 --> 51:59.520
Were you cavalry?

51:59.640 --> 52:02.440
You won the Distinguished Service Medal.

52:02.560 --> 52:03.600
That'll help.

52:04.880 --> 52:05.880
With what?

52:07.320 --> 52:09.760
Two months ago, I was in Rome.

52:09.880 --> 52:11.200
I met Mr Mussolini.

52:12.320 --> 52:14.000
You and I and men like him...

52:16.360 --> 52:18.040
...we will shape the future.

52:20.480 --> 52:22.400
When will you resign
from the Labour Party?

52:25.240 --> 52:28.040
The day before I announce
the formation of my new party.

52:30.960 --> 52:35.880
The British Union of Fascists will be born
on January 1 st of next year.

52:37.000 --> 52:38.480
The first day of a new decade.

52:41.080 --> 52:44.280
The 1930s, Mr Shelby, will belong to us.

52:47.200 --> 52:48.560
Did you bring that cigar?

52:52.080 --> 52:53.160
Before we smoke...

52:54.400 --> 52:55.760
...I have some conditions.

52:58.120 --> 53:00.520
It really isn't going to be
that kind of relationship.

53:04.640 --> 53:07.120
Just smoke like the fine man
you will become.

53:15.720 --> 53:18.400
(BIG BEN CHIMES)

53:22.880 --> 53:24.880
Yes, Colonel Ben Younger.

53:25.000 --> 53:27.920
I have an allocated confidential line -
code 78.

53:30.400 --> 53:32.280
It's me. (CLEARS HIS THROAT)

53:32.400 --> 53:34.280
I've agreed to work with our friend.

53:35.560 --> 53:38.040
He's gonna announce on January 1 st.

53:38.160 --> 53:41.160
I need to know that my position
as informant against him

53:41.280 --> 53:42.520
is officially sanctioned.

53:47.920 --> 53:50.160
(BAND PLAYS)

53:50.280 --> 53:52.600
Today, gentlemen,

53:52.720 --> 53:56.280
we are avenging an unprovoked attack

53:56.400 --> 53:58.720
on members of our organisation

53:58.840 --> 54:02.800
who were simply carrying out
a routine border patrol.

54:02.920 --> 54:05.240
Our enemies are Gypsies,

54:05.360 --> 54:10.080
members of a race destined
for natural eradication anyway,

54:10.200 --> 54:13.400
due to what the scientists call selection.

54:14.840 --> 54:18.960
And since these beggars
are unchristened and unregistered,

54:19.080 --> 54:21.440
the local constabulary
will as soon drop them

54:21.560 --> 54:25.440
in a communal grave
as find a name for a gravestone.

54:26.960 --> 54:32.160
So proceed in any manner you choose
to find the fugitive we seek.

54:38.320 --> 54:40.520
(PISTOL COCKS)

54:40.640 --> 54:42.360
Morning, Mr Gold.

54:42.480 --> 54:44.280
- (BAND APPROACHES)
. Yeah.

54:44.400 --> 54:46.320
The Billy Boys are coming for you.

54:46.440 --> 54:48.080
How the fuck did you find me?

54:49.680 --> 54:52.080
- How the fuck did they find me?
- I kind of let it slip.

54:52.200 --> 54:54.200
Give you no choice, eh?

54:54.320 --> 54:56.480
What, hmm? What?

55:05.120 --> 55:07.320
And a Bentley outside, the engine running.

55:07.440 --> 55:09.800
Fastest engine in the world,
apparently, which is good.

55:09.920 --> 55:12.760
We've got two minutes to get out of here.

55:12.880 --> 55:15.160
(BAND AND ENGINE STOP)

55:31.360 --> 55:35.320
We are officers of
the East Lanarkshire Special Constabulary.

55:35.440 --> 55:38.920
We are seeking a man
by the name of Aberama Gold.

55:40.760 --> 55:44.760
Hand the gentleman over,
and no-one else will be harmed.

56:18.200 --> 56:20.800
Fuck! Take cover!

56:51.160 --> 56:53.000
So, Tommy Shelby...

56:53.120 --> 56:54.800
(INHALES)

56:54.920 --> 56:56.360
...it's war you want...

56:59.080 --> 57:01.120
...it's war you shall have.

57:01.144 --> 57:06.144
http://hiqve.com/
